AGENT eNEWSLETTER



























2016 Commission Changes Overview
 



The Hartford is the market leader in understanding and meeting the personal insurance needs of the preferred mature market (age 50+). We recognize the value our agents provide to preferred mature customers, and we remain committed to the Independent Agency channel, its agents, and its long-term success. Here is a summary of commission changes communicated in March, 2016.
  
In early March, The Hartford's Personal Lines notified Master Code locations that beginning June 1, 2016, our commission program will be assessed at the agency location level. (Commission schedules may differ within an agency's hierarchy.)
Four revised base commission schedules are assigned based upon: 1. profitability, 2. production, and 3. the available opportunity and level of partnership to grow within our niche appetite of the preferred 50+ market. 
The highest base commission will be paid to agency locations demonstrating a shared focus on profitable growth and leveraging the exclusivity of our AARP Through Agents product to be a long-term partner with The Hartford.
We will continue to reevaluate commission schedule assignments periodically as agency location business results and partnerships evolve.
Thank you for your continued partnership and for the business you place with The Hartford Personal Lines.


 

As a reminder, You are expected to comply with all applicable laws, including any pertaining to disclosure of compensation, and You are permitted to disclose to insureds and to prospects the terms of any compensation payable by Us.   You are also expected to update any previous disclosures to insureds or prospects of the compensation payable to You by Us for policies to which your Compensation Plan applies.













 



















